## Detailed Component Design

### 1. `upload.middleware.js`
- Multer `memStorage` (in-memory buffer, no disk writes needed)
- `fileFilter`: accept only `application/pdf` ‚Üí reject others with clean 400 error
- `limits.fileSize`: 10MB max

### 2. `pdf.service.js`
- Uses `pdf-parse` to extract text from `buffer`
- Returns `{ text, pageCount }` or throws on empty/corrupt

### 3. `chunker.service.js`
- Splits text into chunks of **~800 tokens / ~3200 chars** with **200 char overlap**
- Returns array of `{ text, index }` objects

### 4. `embedding.service.js`
- Uses `MistralAI` embeddings model (`mistral-embed`)
- Batch-embeds all chunks (groups of 20 to respect rate limits)
- Returns array of vectors

### 5. `pinecone.service.js`
- Connects using `@pinecone-database/pinecone` (already installed)
- **Index name**: `rag-documents` (add `PINECONE_INDEX` to `.env`)
- **Namespace strategy**: `user-{userId}` per user ‚Üí secure isolation
- `upsertChunks(vectors, metadata)` ‚Äî upsert all chunk vectors
- `queryChunks(queryVector, fileId, userId, topK=5)` ‚Äî filtered retrieval by `fileId` + `userId`
- `deleteFileChunks(fileId, userId)` ‚Äî cleanup on file removal

### 6. `classifier.service.js`
- Uses a **lightweight Mistral prompt** to classify a user query as `FILE_RELATED` or `GENERAL`
- Context given: the uploaded file name
- Fast, cheap, deterministic prompt: returns `true/false` in ~100ms
- Falls back to `GENERAL` on timeout/error

### 7. `rag.service.js`
- Orchestrates the full query pipeline:
  1. Classify query intent
  2. If `GENERAL` ‚Üí return `null` (caller falls back to normal LLM)
  3. If `FILE_RELATED` ‚Üí embed query ‚Üí query Pinecone ‚Üí retrieve top-5 chunks ‚Üí build grounded prompt ‚Üí call Gemini ‚Üí return answer

### 8. `file.controller.js`
- `POST /api/files/upload`: receive PDF ‚Üí extract ‚Üí chunk ‚Üí embed ‚Üí upsert ‚Üí respond `{ fileId, fileName, chunkCount }`
- `DELETE /api/files/:fileId`: delete all vectors for this file from Pinecone

### 9. `ai.service.js` addition
- `generateRagResponse(question, retrievedChunks, memoryContext)` ‚Äî Gemini call with document-grounded prompt
- Tells model: "Answer ONLY from these excerpts. If not found, say so."

### 10. `chat.controller.js` update
- Accept optional `fileId` in `sendMessage` body
- If `fileId` present ‚Üí call `ragService.handleQuery(message, fileId, userId)`
- If returns `null` (general question) ‚Üí continue normal flow
- All existing logic (memory, title gen, message save) remains identical

